INSERT INTO marketing_content_tracker (client_id, platform, date, post_type, script, status, link, time, caption, views, likes, comments, shares, saves, follows, avg_watch_time_pct, boosted, engagement_rate_pct, save_rate_pct, content_score, youtube_views, youtube_watch_time, youtube_avg_view_duration, youtube_ctr, source) VALUES (2, 'instagram', '2026-05-07', 'Reel', 'Reel 7 : PCOS and PCOD
Ref Link :  https://youtube.com/shorts/n75gZdGjjYA?si=c0keqSbq-8H9FlTx
, https://youtube.com/shorts/JzmV09BiOPo?si=9TDJQlH8jI2itBWR

Hook (0-3s): Stop treating PCOS and PCOD like they’re the same thing. You’re likely following advice for a condition you don’t even have.

Loop Opener (3-8s): In 1935, two doctors noticed a specific pattern of "pearl-like" cysts on ovaries. They called it a syndrome, but they accidentally lumped a common imbalance with a lifelong metabolic war.

Middle Build (8-45s): Here’s the breakdown that your 10-minute doctor’s visit probably missed. 

PCOD is a digestive and hormonal "traffic jam." Your ovaries release immature eggs that turn into cysts, usually because of lifestyle or stress. It’s super common—affecting roughly 10% to 15% of women—and it’s often reversible with the right habits. 

PCOS, however? That’s the "glitch in the matrix." It’s an endocrine disorder where your body produces excess androgens (male hormones). The twist? You can have PCOS without ever having a single cyst on your ovaries. One is a localized reproductive hurdle; the other is a full-body metabolic fire that affects your insulin, your hair, and your skin. If you’re treating PCOS with just a "clean diet," you’re fighting a wildfire with a water pistol.

Loop Close (45-57s): So, when you see those "Cure your PCOS" influencers, remember: PCOD is a manageable chapter, but PCOS is a complex internal blueprint. That’s why your "one-size-fits-all" treatment has been failing you.

**CTA (57-60s):** Comment "CHART" and I’ll send you the symptom checklist to help you figure out which one you’re actually dealing with.', 'Posted', 'https://youtube.com/shorts/_v6efUd-YV8 , https://www.instagram.com/reel/DYOop4lDg6_/?igsh=MWw4dDZsMG40M2d3bg==', '12:30', 'PCOS and PCOD are NOT the same thing and confusing them could delay the right treatment. ⚠️

PCOD is commonly linked to lifestyle, stress, and hormonal imbalance where immature eggs form cysts in the ovaries. In many cases, it can improve with the right diet, exercise, and medical support.

PCOS, however, is a deeper endocrine and metabolic disorder. It can affect your hormones, insulin resistance, skin, weight, ovulation, and fertility even if there are no ovarian cysts present.

This is why one-size-fits-all advice on Instagram often fails. Your body deserves a diagnosis that’s accurate, personalized, and science-backed. 💙

At Janya Fertility, HSR Layout Bangalore, Dr. Prathiba focuses on understanding the root cause behind irregular periods, infertility, hormonal imbalance, and PCOS symptoms - So your treatment plan actually works for you.

📍 Janya Fertility – HSR Layout, Bangalore
📩 Save this post for future reference and share it with someone confused between PCOS and PCOD.

