Ref link: 
https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSM5ikWDGjF/?igsh=MTZoZ2k5MXZ6aGl0dg==        
---




Ragi — nine out of ten. One small bowl has more calcium than a full glass of milk. We''ve somehow decided it''s too old-fashioned to eat. Bring it back.

Dahi — eight out of ten. Easy calcium, good gut health, you''re probably already having it. Keep going.

Til — eight and a half. Sesame seeds. Tiny, but the calcium content is kind of ridiculous. Nobody talks about this one enough.

Palak — six out of ten. Good iron, decent calcium, but the oxalates in spinach actually block some of that calcium from absorbing properly. So it''s good. Just not as good as you think.

Methi — seven and a half out of ten. You''re putting it in your paratha, your dal, your sabzi — and honestly it''s quietly doing a lot. Calcium, iron, vitamin K all together.

Rajma — seven out of ten. Good magnesium, some calcium, and magnesium is actually what helps your body use the calcium properly. So this one''s doing background work most people don''t realise.

Chana — seven out of ten. Same story as rajma basically. Good plant-based calcium, good magnesium, easy to add to anything. Don''t underestimate your dal.

Almonds — seven out of ten. Magnesium again, some calcium. A small handful is enough. You don''t need to overdo it.

Milk — seven out of ten. Reliable, not exceptional. There are better sources on this list — which genuinely surprises people.

Amla — eight out of ten. And this one''s not even for calcium directly. Amla is loaded with vitamin C, and vitamin C is what helps your body actually absorb the iron and calcium from everything else you''re eating. So if you''re skipping amla, your other foods aren''t working as hard as they should be. That''s the one most people miss."

"And here''s what I want you to sit with. You''re not just building your baby''s skeleton right now. You''re either protecting your own bones or slowly depleting them. The women I see with osteoporosis in their fifties — a lot of them had pregnancies where nobody told them this. Your diet right now is doing two jobs. Make sure it actually knows that."


"Rate your plate — because your bones are keeping score."

