"If you were diagnosed with PCOS... that condition doesn''t exist anymore."

"Not because you got better. Because they found out the name was wrong the whole time — and so was what you thought was happening inside your body."

"So this year, PCOS got officially renamed. PMOS — polyendocrine metabolic ovarian syndrome, which, yeah, is a mouthful. But the reason behind the name change is the wild part. Researchers actually went back and checked — and there''s no increase in ovarian cysts in this condition. Like, at all. The ''cysts'' you''ve been picturing in your head this whole time? Never really there the way you thought."

"So if you''ve spent years picturing your body as something with a problem growing inside it — that picture was wrong. It’s not  your fault, it is just outdated information. What you actually have is a hormonal and metabolic condition. One that touches way more than your ovaries — skin, weight, energy, all of it. Which, honestly, changes the whole approach. Not ''manage the cysts.'' Manage the system. See what I did there?"

It’s the Same body just a different understanding. And honestly? That''s the first time this diagnosis has made you feel less broken instead of more."

"If you''ve been managing PCOS for years and nobody''s updated you on this — drop a 🙋 and I''ll walk you through what it actually means for you."
