Ref link: 

"You''re in your ninth month. And suddenly the baby feels like it''s moving less. And you''re scared.

🎬 **Visual:** Dr. Prathiba direct to camera. Quiet, warm. No graphics, no text. Just her face — matches the viewer''s emotional state exactly.
Here''s something nobody tells you — when you''re walking around all day, your movement is literally rocking the baby to sleep inside you. So of course you don''t feel much. The moment you sit down and rest? That''s when they wake up."*

🎬 **Visual:** Simple animation — mother walking, baby curled inside gently swaying. Then mother sits. Baby stirs. No text needed, the visual tells it.
In the sixth or seventh month there''s so much fluid — the baby is doing full flips, rolls, kicks at 2am. You''re lying there thinking, is this child going to be the next Ronaldo? or Messi? You might think — because we all know who''s better with their kicks. But by the ninth month? They''ve grown so much, the head is locked down, there''s barely room to turn. The big rolls and kicks stop. What you get instead is — honestly, it almost hurts sometimes. Sharp jabs. A push from the inside that you weren''t expecting. That''s your baby, fully formed, just running out of space. That''s not a warning sign. That''s actually a good sign."*

