Here''s what to actually track. After every meal — eat, then lie down. Just rest. Your blood sugar goes up, that glucose reaches the baby, and they get this little burst of energy. In that one hour, if you feel 3 to 4 movements — that''s fine. You''re fine. Across the whole day, 8 to 10 movements total. That''s basically your number now. Not constant movement like before. Just that."* Your baby didn''t get quieter because something is wrong. They got quieter because they grew. There''s a difference."
Any concerns in your ninth month — call us at my clinic, the contact is in my bio. We''re here."*

